It's believed Megan de Lange was abducted in the early hours Thursday morning by a man suspected to be her biological father. JOHANNESBURG - A six-day-old baby has been abducted from her Richards Bay home in KwaZulu-Natal. It's believed Megan de Lange was abducted in the early hours Thursday morning by a man suspected to be her biological father. Missing Children South Africa's Bianca Van Aswegen said: “We appeal to the public to please assist us. Anyone with information can contact the South African Police Service or Missing Children South Africa. The alleged father also left with a black vehicle with GP number plates.” De Lange was last seen wearing a baby pink vest and grey pants. Her family is calling on anyone with information about her disappearance to contact police. 